@NODE Intro "Introduction"

INTRODUCTION


 vdisk.device is a driver for a recoverable RAM disk. It started in 1993 as
a hack of ASDG-RAM (written by Perry S. Kivolowitz). These hacked versions 
(1.3 -> 1.12) were not distributed.
 As of version 2.0, it has been entirely rewritten, with many new features added :

@{CODE}
 - Up to 16 units with virtually unlimited size (theoretical limit is 4 Gb)
 - Sector size of 512, 1024 or 2048 bytes (version 3 and up)
 - Dynamic memory allocation and (optionnaly) deallocation
 - Full support of standard AmigaDOS Filesystems (DOS\0 to DOS\5).
 - Will survive the heaviest system crashes as long as its own data is not 
   corrupted.
 - In case of a recovery failure, the cause can be reported by a support command.
 - Automounting/Autobooting units are now supported as of V3.3.
 - Volatile units that don't keep their content across reboots are supported as
   of V3.5.
@{BODY}

 VDisk requires AmigaOS 2.04 or higher (V37). For the new AUTOMOUNT/AUTOBOOT
features, the vdisk.device must be installed as a resident module with Thomas
Richter's LoadModule command, available on Aminet as util/boot/LoadModule.lha.
Version 40.10 or higher of LoadModule is required, earlier versions are broken
and will not work.

 VDisk has been developed independently from StatRam (Another ASDG-RAM based
ram drive written by Richard Waspe and Nicola Salmoria, apparently no longer
supported). It has been heavily tested on the following system configurations:

@{CODE}
 - A4000T 68060 AGA + CV64/3D (Picasso96), 2 Mb Chip 144 Mb Fast, OS 3.9
   1 Gb + 4 Gb SCSI HDs + 9.5 Gb IDE HD
 - A500 68000 ECS , 1 Mb Chip 1.5 Mb Slow 2 Mb Fast, OS 3.1
   20 Mb IDE-XT + 50 Mb + 115 Mb SCSI HDs
 - A4000 68040 AGA + CV64/3D (CGfx 3), 2 Mb Chip 16 Mb Fast, OS 3.9
   250 Mb + 165 Mb IDE HDs + 1 Gb + 512 Mb + 2.8 Gb SCSI HDs
 - A3000 68030/68882 ECS, 2 Mb Chip 16 Mb Fast, OS 3.5
   100 Mb + 2 Gb + 4 Gb + 8.6 Gb SCSI HDs
 - A500 68040(PP&S) ECS , 1 Mb Chip 2 Mb Fast16 8 Mb Fast32, OS 2.1
   165 Mb SCSI HD
@{BODY}

@ENDNODE
